<div class="panel-body list-group collapse out" data-propname="RisksOfTest" id="article-RisksOfTest" role="tabpanel" style="display: none;">
<h2>Risks of a bone ablation</h2>
<p>Bone ablation is usually a low-risk procedure. The risk may increase depending on your childâ€™s condition, age and health, and the location of the osteoid osteoma.</p>
<p>The risks of a bone ablation can include:</p>
<ul>
<li>skin burn</li>
<li>infection (bone, joint or skin)</li>
<li>fracture (break) of the bone</li>
<li>blood vessel or nerve damage</li>
<li>injury to any organ nearby</li>
</ul> </div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div aria-controls="article-PreparingForProcedure" aria-expanded="false" class="panel-heading clickable rs_preserve" role="button" tabindex="0">
<span class="panel-heading-collapsable">Preparing for the procedure</span>
<span class="pull-right panel-heading-collapsable-icon" href="#article-PreparingForProcedure">
